  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Agricultural Development: Joint Programme for the Sahel in Response to the Challenges of COVID-19, Conflict and Climate Change</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Objective is to &quot;consolidate the means of existence
small producers, in particular women and young people living in areas
cross-border &#xBF;by adopting sustainable production practices and cohesion approaches
social and gender transformation. The program in Chad will reach a total of 11,000
agro-pastoral households over the 6 years for a total of about 66,000 people, 50% of whom are
women, 40% of young people, who will participate in various initiatives to increase their capacity
resilience. The first 3-year phase will concern 6,000 households for a total of 36,000
people</narrative>
  </description>
